summary:
- Speaker A tells the psychiatrist that he feels ineffective and unable in the job because he is too refined for the place.
- Speaker A wants a relationship with someone that will strengthen her to fight what's in her mind. She wants to find some way of coming out of the hole of really resolving a relationship, not just having it chopped off.
- The place she works in is exploiting the negro people. She thinks she is unattractive and she is afraid to go to the studio to paint and draw because she thinks the fellow who runs the studio is oppressive.
- Speaker A thinks the hook could have come up because she went back to him. But she is afraid when she gets this upset for fear it will go into action.
- Speaker A tells B that hooks in the head must serve some purpose. The only experience of a hook was when she had a misplacement of the uterus.
- Dr. Rogers asks her to talk about her feelings about her husband and her disappointment and hatred of Bill. She tries to make a last ditch fight by trying to work and organize around nothing. She wants her mother to take care of her.
